23/01/2020

Get access to data regarding queues in municipal offices in Warsaw

The city hall of Warsaw made a variety of data public here. Everyone is welcome to access the data via API, using JSON file format. One of the datasets contains the information about queues in municipal offices in Warsaw, ie. expected times, open counters and amount of people waiting.

kolejkeR is an R wrapper around the API, developed as a project for Advanced R classes at the Warsaw University of Technology. It's suitable both for further data processing and analysis, as well as for quick acquirement of information helpful for everyday life in Warsaw.

Whats new?

  • SHINY
  • AppVeyor
  • Amount of dependencies reduced
  • Dataset of archived data for your own exploration
  • New function for collecting all data
  • Model for predictions

New function

append_api_data_to_csv(filename)
  1. Collects data from Warsaw queue api from all offices
  2. Writes it to csv file

Where the service time is the longest?

Dataset

Package function were used to gather data about queues in Warsaw's government offices. Data was collected on the span of couple of weeks from December 28 to January 22. Warsaw's office API was called repeatedly every 5 minutes and results appended to csv file. KolejkeR package includes this dataset in a form of a data frame with 830172 rows and 12 variables. Uncompressed csv file with dataset takes 84.3 MB of memory.
